data.title: DePauw Competes at Rose
data.meta_description: Stories, updates and press releases from DePauw University.
data.text:
DePauw Competes at Rose-Hulman Twilight

April 18, 2008

April 18, 2008, Terre Haute, Ind. - Several Tigers competed at the Rose-Hulman Twilight led by Ryan McElwain's third-place showing in the shot put at 13.66 meters (44-9.75) and fourth place finish in the discus at 39.52 meters (129-8).

Robert Steele was fourth in the javelin with a throw of 43.37 meters (142-3), while Thomas Moore finished fifth in the hammer at 40.29 meters (132-2). Tyler Doane placed fifth in the shot put (12.98 m; 42-7) as did Jake Sweeney in the 800 meters in 1:59.83.

DePauw hosts the Southern Collegiate Athletic Conference Championships on Friday and Saturday, April 25-26.

Licensed to Rose-Hulman Institute of Technology Hy-Tek's Meet Manager 4/20/2008 10:04 AM 2008 Rose-Hulman Twiligh Meet - 4/18/2008 Rose-Hulman Institute of Technology William M.
